					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "It seems the issue is that GT might be running a non-interactive shell, which doesn't source user configuration files like /.bashrc or /.bash_profile. This causes the PATH to miss necessary tools like npm. To fix this, I suggest two options:\n\n    Use npx with a full path or package bin path.\n\n    Ensure GT uses the environment of a Nix dev shell. You could create a wrapper script that calls direnv exec to inject the environment, ensuring that GT can access the correct PATH.\n\nManaging environment in GT\n\nIt looks like GT might not be getting the right PATH for npm due to its shell process running with a limited or non-interactive environment. To fix this, we could modify their gt wrapper or set the PATH using GT's \"Bindings\" for Shell Process. Alternatively, I could suggest using bash -lc to load the login shell, which reads /.bash_profile. A Smalltalk code snippet like this might work:\n"
