				},
				"string" : "Fixing npm not found in GT\n\nThe error \"npm not found\" likely means that npm isn't in the GT shell process' environment. To resolve this, you can update the PATH variable in GT’s Bindings. If using Node through Nix, try paths like /.nix-profile/bin/npm or /etc/profiles/per-user/user/bin/npm. For Homebrew on macOS, typical paths are /opt/homebrew/bin/npm (for Apple Silicon) or /usr/local/bin/npm (for Intel)."
